{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1178,"text":"How much do you get paid?"},{"time":3155,"text":"Don't answer that out loud."},{"time":5666,"text":"But put a number in your head."},{"time":8017,"text":"Now: How much do you think the person\nsitting next to you gets paid?"},{"time":13176,"text":"Again, don't answer out loud."}]},{"cues":[{"time":15359,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":17144,"text":"At work, how much do you think"},{"time":19526,"text":"the person sitting in the cubicle\nor the desk next to you gets paid?"},{"time":23488,"text":"Do you know?"},{"time":24977,"text":"Should you know?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":26961,"text":"Notice, it's a little uncomfortable for me\nto even ask you those questions."},{"time":30962,"text":"But admit it -- you kind of want to know."},{"time":34993,"text":"Most of us are uncomfortable with the idea\nof broadcasting our salary."},{"time":38542,"text":"We're not supposed to tell our neighbors,"},{"time":40715,"text":"and we're definitely not supposed\nto tell our office neighbors."},{"time":43931,"text":"The assumed reason is that if everybody\nknew what everybody got paid,"},{"time":47469,"text":"then all hell would break loose."},{"time":49283,"text":"There'd be arguments, there'd be fights,"},{"time":51408,"text":"there might even be a few people who quit."},{"time":53621,"text":"But what if secrecy is actually\nthe reason for all that strife?"},{"time":57424,"text":"And what would happen\nif we removed that secrecy?"},{"time":60599,"text":"What if openness actually increased\nthe sense of fairness and collaboration"},{"time":64614,"text":"inside a company?"},{"time":65860,"text":"What would happen if we had\ntotal pay transparency?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":70254,"text":"For the past several years,"},{"time":71595,"text":"I've been studying the corporate\nand entrepreneurial leaders"},{"time":74532,"text":"who question the conventional wisdom\nabout how to run a company."},{"time":78105,"text":"And the question of pay keeps coming up."},{"time":81105,"text":"And the answers keep surprising."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84458,"text":"It turns out that pay transparency --"},{"time":86289,"text":"sharing salaries openly\nacross a company --"},{"time":88423,"text":"makes for a better workplace\nfor both the employee"},{"time":91096,"text":"and for the organization."},{"time":93362,"text":"When people don't know how their pay\ncompares to their peers',"},{"time":96485,"text":"they're more likely to feel underpaid"},{"time":98325,"text":"and maybe even discriminated against."},{"time":100646,"text":"Do you want to work at a place\nthat tolerates the idea"},{"time":103245,"text":"that you feel underpaid\nor discriminated against?"},{"time":106697,"text":"But keeping salaries secret\ndoes exactly that,"},{"time":109231,"text":"and it's a practice\nas old as it is common,"},{"time":112674,"text":"despite the fact\nthat in the United States,"},{"time":114790,"text":"the law protects an employee's right\nto discuss their pay."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119417,"text":"In one famous example from decades ago,"},{"time":121999,"text":"the management of Vanity Fair magazine"},{"time":124129,"text":"actually circulated a memo entitled:"},{"time":126273,"text":"\"Forbidding Discussion Among\nEmployees of Salary Received.\""},{"time":129502,"text":"\"Forbidding\" discussion among\nemployees of salary received."},{"time":133482,"text":"Now that memo didn't sit well\nwith everybody."},{"time":135653,"text":"New York literary figures\nDorothy Parker,"},{"time":137723,"text":"Robert Benchley and Robert Sherwood,"},{"time":139509,"text":"all writers in the Algonquin Round Table,"},{"time":141974,"text":"decided to stand up for transparency"},{"time":143779,"text":"and showed up for work the next day"},{"time":145535,"text":"with their salary written on signs\nhanging from their neck."}]},{"cues":[{"time":148773,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":150716,"text":"Imagine showing up for work"},{"time":152315,"text":"with your salary just written\nacross your chest for all to see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":157573,"text":"But why would a company even want\nto discourage salary discussions?"},{"time":160867,"text":"Why do some people go along with it,\nwhile others revolt against it?"},{"time":165906,"text":"It turns out that in addition\nto the assumed reasons,"},{"time":168974,"text":"pay secrecy is actually a way\nto save a lot of money."},{"time":172301,"text":"You see, keeping salaries secret"},{"time":174236,"text":"leads to what economists call\n\"information asymmetry.\""},{"time":177211,"text":"This is a situation where,\nin a negotiation,"},{"time":179506,"text":"one party has loads more\ninformation than the other."},{"time":182887,"text":"And in hiring or promotion\nor annual raise discussions,"},{"time":186321,"text":"an employer can use that secrecy\nto save a lot of money."},{"time":190518,"text":"Imagine how much better\nyou could negotiate for a raise"},{"time":193166,"text":"if you knew everybody's salary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197612,"text":"Economists warn that information asymmetry"},{"time":200077,"text":"can cause markets to go awry."},{"time":201748,"text":"Someone leaves a pay stub on the copier,"},{"time":203678,"text":"and suddenly everybody\nis shouting at each other."},{"time":206866,"text":"In fact, they even warn"},{"time":208596,"text":"that information asymmetry\ncan lead to a total market failure."},{"time":214095,"text":"And I think we're almost there."},{"time":216133,"text":"Here's why:"},{"time":217323,"text":"first, most employees have no idea\nhow their pay compares to their peers'."},{"time":222834,"text":"In a 2015 survey of 70,000 employees,"},{"time":226708,"text":"two-thirds of everyone who is paid\nat the market rate"},{"time":230113,"text":"said that they felt they were underpaid."},{"time":233036,"text":"And of everybody who felt\nthat they were underpaid,"},{"time":235939,"text":"60 percent said\nthat they intended to quit,"},{"time":238916,"text":"regardless of where they were --\nunderpaid, overpaid"},{"time":241828,"text":"or right at the market rate."},{"time":244200,"text":"If you were part of this survey,\nwhat would you say?"},{"time":246684,"text":"Are you underpaid?"},{"time":247984,"text":"Well, wait -- how do you even know,"},{"time":250333,"text":"because you're not allowed\nto talk about it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":252911,"text":"Next, information asymmetry, pay secrecy,"},{"time":256534,"text":"makes it easier to ignore\nthe discrimination"},{"time":259337,"text":"that's already present\nin the market today."},{"time":262217,"text":"In a 2011 report from the Institute\nfor Women's Policy Research,"},{"time":265938,"text":"the gender wage gap\nbetween men and women"},{"time":268086,"text":"was 23 percent."},{"time":270451,"text":"This is where that 77 cents\non the dollar comes from."},{"time":273641,"text":"But in the Federal Government,"},{"time":275128,"text":"where salaries are pinned\nto certain levels"},{"time":277215,"text":"and everybody knows\nwhat those levels are,"},{"time":279279,"text":"the gender wage gap\nshrinks to 11 percent --"},{"time":281388,"text":"and this is before controlling\nfor any of the factors"},{"time":283988,"text":"that economists argue over\nwhether or not to control for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287264,"text":"If we really want to close\nthe gender wage gap,"},{"time":289960,"text":"maybe we should start\nby opening up the payroll."},{"time":292864,"text":"If this is what total\nmarket failure looks like,"},{"time":296110,"text":"then openness remains\nthe only way to ensure fairness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300274,"text":"Now, I realize that letting people\nknow what you make"},{"time":302799,"text":"might feel uncomfortable,"},{"time":304469,"text":"but isn't it less uncomfortable"},{"time":306008,"text":"than always wondering\nif you're being discriminated against,"},{"time":308912,"text":"or if your wife or your daughter\nor your sister is being paid unfairly?"},{"time":313353,"text":"Openness remains the best way\nto ensure fairness,"},{"time":317317,"text":"and pay transparency does that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319991,"text":"That's why entrepreneurial leaders\nand corporate leaders"},{"time":322695,"text":"have been experimenting\nwith sharing salaries for years."},{"time":325512,"text":"Like Dane Atkinson."},{"time":326949,"text":"Dane is a serial entrepreneur\nwho started many companies"},{"time":330852,"text":"in a pay secrecy condition"},{"time":332458,"text":"and even used that condition\nto pay two equally qualified people"},{"time":335835,"text":"dramatically different salaries,"},{"time":337555,"text":"depending on how well\nthey could negotiate."},{"time":340091,"text":"And Dane saw the strife\nthat happened as a result of this."},{"time":343888,"text":"So when he started\nhis newest company, SumAll,"},{"time":346139,"text":"he committed to salary transparency\nfrom the beginning."},{"time":349821,"text":"And the results have been amazing."},{"time":352424,"text":"And in study after study,"},{"time":354070,"text":"when people know\nhow they're being paid"},{"time":355970,"text":"and how that pay compares to their peers',"},{"time":358023,"text":"they're more likely to work hard\nto improve their performance,"},{"time":360980,"text":"more likely to be engaged,\nand they're less likely to quit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363853,"text":"That's why Dane's not alone."},{"time":365279,"text":"From technology start-ups like Buffer,"},{"time":367915,"text":"to the tens of thousands\nof employees at Whole Foods,"},{"time":371285,"text":"where not only is your salary\navailable for everyone to see,"},{"time":374476,"text":"but the performance data\nfor the store and for your department"},{"time":377500,"text":"is available on the company intranet"},{"time":379443,"text":"for all to see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381985,"text":"Now, pay transparency\ntakes a lot of forms."},{"time":384471,"text":"It's not one size fits all."},{"time":386093,"text":"Some post their salaries for all to see."},{"time":388613,"text":"Some only keep it inside the company."},{"time":390938,"text":"Some post the formula for calculating pay,"},{"time":393547,"text":"and others post the pay levels"},{"time":395345,"text":"and affix everybody to that level."},{"time":397147,"text":"So you don't have to make signs"},{"time":399220,"text":"for all of your employees\nto wear around the office."},{"time":401768,"text":"And you don't have to be\nthe only one wearing a sign"},{"time":404706,"text":"that you made at home."},{"time":406494,"text":"But we can all take greater steps\ntowards pay transparency."},{"time":410233,"text":"For those of you that have the authority"},{"time":412285,"text":"to move forward towards transparency:"},{"time":414103,"text":"it's time to move forward."},{"time":415943,"text":"And for those of you\nthat don't have that authority:"},{"time":418435,"text":"it's time to stand up for your right to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":421263,"text":"So how much do you get paid?"},{"time":424186,"text":"And how does that compare\nto the people you work with?"},{"time":427190,"text":"You should know."},{"time":429312,"text":"And so should they."}]},{"cues":[{"time":431936,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":433128,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}